00:02:04.960 --> 00:02:07.410
can they go hand in hand?

00:02:07.410 --> 00:02:10.820
So the current paradigm
is that we produce goods,

00:02:10.820 --> 00:02:14.300
they're used to by the industry,
used by the population,

00:02:14.300 --> 00:02:15.990
and then thrown out.

00:02:15.990 --> 00:02:18.560
What do we do with the wastes?

00:02:18.560 --> 00:02:23.470
So therefore, with the
increase in energy consumption,

00:02:23.470 --> 00:02:27.970
we find that people are using
more energy, creating more

00:02:27.970 --> 00:02:31.180
waste, and as a
result, there's also

00:02:31.180 --> 00:02:33.530
depletion of water resources.

00:02:33.530 --> 00:02:36.470
And we're depleting resources
and increasing wastes.

00:02:36.470 --> 00:02:40.700
